      "content": "While over-the-counter antacids and aspirin may provide some relief, they may not address the underlying cause of your symptoms. Additionally, taking extra antacids without consulting a doctor can lead to an imbalance of essential minerals in your body. It's worth noting that heartburn or acid reflux can be a symptom of an underlying condition, such as gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD). By not addressing the root cause, the issue may worsen over time.",
